Paper: hep-th/9911187

Date: 1999-11-24

Title: Affine Kac-Moody Algebras and the Wess-Zumino-Witten Model

Authors: Mark Walton

Comments: 68 pages, harvmac big, 24 figures, lecture notes, Istanbul, 8/98

These lecture notes are a brief introduction to Wess-Zumino-Witten models,and their current algebras, the affine Kac-Moody algebras. After reviewing thegeneral background, we focus on the application of representation theory to thecomputation of 3-point functions and fusion rules.